{
  "body" : "Design ONE finished commercial sport campaign poster, museum-grade ad agency quality, ready for OOH and social rollout.\n\nSubject\n- Hero: {{subject}}\n- Sport / discipline: {{sport}}\n- Pose must be authentically athletic — peak action, not a model-pretending-to-train cliché. Sweat, muscle tension, fabric stretch and motion blur where appropriate.\n\nHero Prop\n- {{prop}}\n- The prop is structural, not decorative. Specify its angle, scale and position so it becomes a compositional bone of the poster.\n\nComposition\n- Layout: {{layout}}\n- One single, dominant visual idea. No moodboard, no template grid, no presentation board, no collage of multiple poster variants. Single finished poster only.\n- Strong hierarchy: hero subject > prop > headline > supporting copy. Generous negative space. Bleed the subject if needed to create scale.\n\nTypography\n- Headline (must be set huge, spelled exactly, dominant on the poster):\n  \"{{headline}}\"\n- Supporting copy (single line, smaller, near the headline or anchored to a corner):\n  \"{{supporting_copy}}\"\n- Use one custom-feeling sans-serif (heavy condensed or wide industrial), tightly tracked for the headline. No default fonts, no fake-cursive scripts.\n- Do not add any other large readable text beyond what is specified.\n\nColor & Surface\n- Palette: {{color_palette}}. Restrained — 1 dominant + 1 punch accent + 1 neutral.\n- Print finish should feel like a real ad poster: subtle screen grain, ink density, sharp edges. Avoid plastic-3D rendering and over-glossy textures.\n\nLighting\n- Cinematic, directional light. Strong rim or hard top-down to sculpt the body. Reflective floor or wet asphalt is encouraged when it strengthens the silhouette.\n\nBrand polish\n- This must read as a high-end brand campaign (think Nike / On / Adidas / Lululemon flagship), not stock advertising. Premium, intentional, slightly cinematic, never cheesy.\n\nStrict avoid\n- No generic stock-fitness clichés (gym mirror selfies, lens flares, pixel sparkles).\n- No wrong sport equipment for the discipline (e.g. tennis racket on a basketball court).\n- No misspelled headline. No watermarks, no fake brand logos, no copied real-brand logos.\n- No mosaic of multiple poster options.\n\nOutput aspect ratio: {{aspect_ratio}}.\n\n——————\nSubject: {{subject}}\nSport: {{sport}}\nProp: {{prop}}\nLayout: {{layout}}\nHeadline: {{headline}}\nSupporting copy: {{supporting_copy}}\nPalette: {{color_palette}}\nAspect: {{aspect_ratio}}\n",
